reviews.author_name: Habitual Fare Dodger Who Doesn't Pay His TV Licence
reviews.text: Staff are charming, polite and helpful, an asset to Southeastern railway, particulary the rotund, middle-aged fellow with the floppy grey hair and winning smile. Top geezer. Ten season tickets out of Five, will surely use again

I use this station regularly, I don't like Canterbury but I have to give this station 5 stars for the world best platform manager, last Thursday. 

"if you see anything suspicious other then my hair cut, then please report it too the police"

Its good to see staff that have a good sense of humour.

Like most railways in the uk it can be costly but this especially was a unwelcomed cost. Dont usually mind about the cost but the man at the till with grey hair was very rude and when I asked a question he stared at me like a moron. He needs customer service training.

Having just a few minutes before my train I mistakenly bought a single ticket instead of an open return. The man at the ticket office quickly changed the ticked for me in time to catch my train. He will probably never see this but - thank you so much.
A standard train station with basic amenities, has a cozy rest area, a small supermarket and cafe, with two platforms.
